name: Wiz
summary: Israeli cybersecurity firm Wiz has declined a $23 billion acquisition offer from Alphabet, the parent company of Google. This move comes after negotiations between the two companies reportedly ended over price and other deal terms. Wiz is now planning to pursue an initial public offering (IPO) instead. The acquisition, if it had gone through, would have marked the largest deal in Google's history. Wiz's rejection highlights the growing trend of cybersecurity firms opting for IPOs to raise capital and secure long-term growth.

name: Olympics
summary: The 2024 Paris Olympics are fast approaching, with preparations and anticipation reaching their peak. To excite fans, Global News highlights five key details. Meanwhile, the National Post provides an in-depth look at the grandeur of the Opening Ceremony, set to be the largest in Olympic history. Rumors of celebrity performances swirl, with NBC News and CBC.ca reporting on Celine Dion and Lady Gaga's arrival in Paris. Amidst the excitement, Matt Dawson makes a remarkable sacrifice for his Olympic aspirations, as reported by Olympics. Toronto Star publishes a comprehensive list of Canadian athletes competing in the Games. Al Jazeera English offers a comprehensive guide to the event, including schedule, sports, venues, and dates. In a thought-provoking piece, The Guardian proposes innovative ways to enhance the Olympics, including adding a burger-stacking contest. CTV News Calgary highlights southern Alberta athletes representing Canada, and CBC.ca raises concerns about a French hijab ban in sports, calling it a "shameful moment" as the country prepares to host the Games.
